      • toFile

        public abstract void toFile(java.util.List<MatchedPair> list,
                            java.lang.String filename,
                            int summaryType)
        Takes in a list of matched pairs, and local path/filename for the output file, and the summary type requested by the user, and saves the data to a file of their choosing. By default the results are printed to the console if no output file is given.
        Parameters:
        list - an array list of matched pairs
        filename - a local path/filename for the output file
        summaryType - an integer corresponding to a summary type
